6000|$|<b>Wise.</b> It was <b>enough</b> {{to do it}} indeed, yea it did effectually do it. It {{killed her}} in time, yea {{it was all the}} time a killing of her. She would often-times when she sate by her self, thus mournfully bewail her condition: {77b} Wo is me that I sojourn in Meshech, and that I dwell in the tents of Kedar; my soul hath long time dwelt with him that hateth peace. {77c} O what shall be given unto thee, thou {{deceitful}} tongue? or what shall be done unto thee, thou false tongue? I am a Woman grieved in spirit, my Husband has bought me and sold me for his lusts: 'Twas not me, but my Money that he wanted: O that he had had it, so I had had my liberty! ...|$|R
